anyone know of a way to get this to configure properly? i get the pop ups every patch and it locks up my machine every time. even trying with window mode. i lose the mouse. the patch the other night i got to work but it involved 7 reboots and a lot of screaming and a broken chair. i will NOT use my machine without a firewall. too many viruses have come at me. help? <p>When your odd, the odds are with you</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ifrinnofthebrood>Ifrinn of the brood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/11/03 8:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1757.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: zonealarm</span><hr size=1> The simplest workaround I've found is to shutdown the firewall, start EQ, log in, put EQ in windowed mode, start ZoneAlarm again. Else, just like you, my system freezes up completely and I have to reboot. If only zoneAlarm was programmered properly, you could move around with the tab and arrow keys, and select 'yes'. But even then EQ just goes bonkers when its connection is interrupted like that.<br>
<br>
Another workaround is to lower your 'program contol' setting to low. Applications no longer need ZoneAlarm approval to access the web; the firewall just monitors net activity. Of couse once in EQ you should put the setting back to medium or high.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ifrinnofthebrood>Ifrinn of the brood</A> at: 7/11/03 9:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coslinroguebarbarian>CoslinRogueBarbarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 376<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/11/03 11:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1757.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: zonealarm</span><hr size=1> Very Odd. I have ZoneAlarm as well and it has never, ever given me problems with EQ. I don't know why, but I seem to have been blessed with easy access.<br>
